# Reed-Solomon-ish syndrome for one-error detection.
*syndrome(codeword as Vec of i64, n as i64, alpha as i64) returns i64
    s is 0
    p is 1
    i is 0
    while i < n
        s is (s + codeword.get(i) * p) % 257
        p is (p * alpha) % 257
        i is i + 1
    s

*main
    cw is vec()
    cw.push(1)
    cw.push(2)
    cw.push(3)
    cw.push(4)
    cw.push(5)
    log syndrome(cw, 5, 3)
